2f8ef455-c009.name: Toyota Avensis 1.6i
2f8ef455-c009.description: Imported from Denmark. 203 000 km with full service history. No blemishes on the paint, well maintained interior, technically sound. Possible lease through leasing company or bank or barter for another car.

3ba2d888-1ce4.name: VW Golf GTI
3ba2d888-1ce4.description: THE PRICE IS NON-NEGOTIABLE!!! Newly imported, 202 799 km, 90hp diesel. Manual transmission.

d7dd8fds-d2g3.name: Mercedes Benz S 500
d7dd8fds-d2g3.description: The 2022 Mercedes-Benz S-class is as much a personal limo for the ultra-wealthy as it is a rolling showcase of the company's latest tech. ... Along with standard all-wheel drive, the S-class's effortless acceleration comes from a 429-hp straight-six (S500) or a 496-hp V-8 (S580).

12c9sf49-4hzd.name: Audi A8
12c9sf49-4hzd.description: The Audi A8 is a full-size luxury sedan manufactured and marketed by the German automaker Audi since 1994. Succeeding the Audi V8, and now in its fourth generation, the A8 has been offered with both front- or permanent all-wheel drive—and in short- and long-wheelbase variants.

0040221f-0ad2.name: Mercedes Benz G 63 AMG
0040221f-0ad2.description: The Mercedes-Benz G-Class, sometimes called G-Wagon (short for Geländewagen, "terrain vehicle"), is a four-wheel drive automobile manufactured by Magna Steyr (formerly Steyr-Daimler-Puch) in Austria and sold by Mercedes-Benz. ... The G-Wagon is characterised by its boxy styling and body-on-frame construction.

3c72a7c1-195c.name: Lamborghini Urus
3c72a7c1-195c.description: Automobili Lamborghini S.p.A. (Italian pronunciation: [autoˈmɔːbili lamborˈɡiːni]) is an Italian brand and manufacturer of luxury sports cars and SUVs based in Sant'Agata Bolognese. The company is owned by the Volkswagen Group through its subsidiary Audi.

681760cd-4964.name: Porsche GT3 RS
681760cd-4964.description: The GT3 RS is a 4.0-litre, naturally-aspirated 911 whose 513bhp engine is a lot like the 911 Cup race car's. There is rose-jointed suspension like a GT2 RS (and Cup car), spring rates close to the 911 Cup's and almost as much downforce as a Cup car.

807e0628-127c.name: Nissan GTR R35
807e0628-127c.description: The Nissan GT-R is a high-performance sports car and grand tourer produced by Nissan that was unveiled in 2007.[3][4][5] It is the successor to the Skyline GT-R, a high performance variant of the Nissan Skyline. Although this car was the sixth-generation model to bear the GT-R name, the model is no longer part of the Nissan Skyline model lineup since that name is now reserved for Nissan's luxury-sport vehicles. The GT-R shares the Nissan FM platform with the separate Nissan Skyline luxury car and the Nissan Z sports car.
